findings.title: Owner can change the tax and liquidity fee
findings.description: The owner has the privilege to modify the tax and liquidity fee, which could lead to potential security risks.

findings.title: Owner can change the maximum transaction amount.
findings.description: The owner has the privilege to modify the maximum transaction amount, which could lead to potential security risks.

findings.title: Owner can exclude from the fee.
findings.description: The owner has the privilege to exclude from the fee, which could lead to potential security issues.

findings.title: Owner Privilege: Modifiable Marketing Divisor
findings.description: The owner has the capability to modify the marketingDivisor, which may lead to unintended consequences.

findings.title: Owner can change minimum number of tokens to add to liquidity
findings.description: The owner has the privilege to modify the minimum number of tokens required to add to liquidity.

findings.title: Owner can change buyBackUpperLimit
findings.description: The owner has the privilege to modify the buyBackUpperLimit, which could lead to potential security risks.

findings.title: Owner can change marketing address.
findings.description: The owner has the privilege to modify the marketing address, which could lead to potential security risks.

findings.title: Owner can enable and disable buyBack
findings.description: The owner has the privilege to enable or disable the buyBack feature.

findings.title: Owner can enable before and after presale modes
findings.description: The owner has the privilege to enable or disable presale modes before and after a specific event.

findings.title: Owner Can Withdraw Contract Funds
findings.description: The owner has the privilege to withdraw contract BNBs and ERC20 tokens to a specific address (0x1F20ed94292200b19B229BD331985FC28f4C3944).

findings.title: Owner Privilege Retake
findings.description: The owner can lock and unlock, allowing them to retake privileges even after ownership renouncement.

findings.title: DoS with block gas limit.
findings.description: The contract may be vulnerable to Denial of Service (DoS) attacks due to the block gas limit, potentially causing transactions to fail or be aborted.
